3. Bound States in the Heavy Mass Limit

Before discussing the exact solutions to the bound state equations emerging from (2.5) for the S- and P wave heavy mesons it is illuminating to review the results associated with the heavy mass limit, i.e. M ! 1 and M

\Lambda

! 1. In that limit the wave-functions receive

their only support at the origin r = 0. Hence the binding energy is given by the negative of the potential for the heavy mesons at the origin. Since this potential is generated by the static soliton the binding energy is extracted from the light meson profiles F; G and ! at r = 0. For this purpose one substitutes the expansions

