Again we observe that in the P-wave case the approximation (A.9) is very good while in the S wave channel the corresponding solution overestimates the exact binding energy. In this respect the behavior of the model is similar to the one without light vector mesons.

We remark that for ff ss 0 numerically stable penta quark solutions in both S and P wave channels are observed. However, these carry binding energies no larger than about 50MeV and hence may well disappear upon modification of the model. The vanishing binding of the penta-quarks for ff ss 0 has already been conjectured in ref. [9] from the fact that

