The Euler-Lagrange equations associated with (A.1) and (A.3) are integrated using the method described in appendix A for ref. [12]. Technically a problem arises because the equation of motion for \Psi

1

is a constraint rather than a second order differential equation as

in the case of the other fields. Hence \Psi

1

is not a dynamical degree of freedom and has to be

eliminated in terms of the other fields. This can be achieved by formally writing

